full_text: In this demonstration, I am going to simulate the invoice process by manually advancing the clock and running two batch processes. Of course, in a production environment, the billing process occurs automatically as time passes and various batch processes are executed according to schedule. Here's the AmeriQuest account. Let's go to the invoices screen. I'll select the invoice. Invoice stream for the GL01 policy. I select the invoice stream. The first invoice has a planned status, so we know that an invoice has not been billed for this policy. The bill date is February 12th. I'll switch to the SuperUser browser to advance the clock to the bill date. I need to advance the clock to February 12th. Invoice stream for the invoice. Now I click Change Date. Next, I'll go to the Server Tools tab. I'll scroll until I see the invoice batch process. Here it is. I click Run. The batch process will look for all invoices with a bill date of today and bill them. Let's go back to Jeff Park to see the result. I'll refresh the display by clicking the second invoice. Notice the status of the first invoice has changed from Plan to Build. This means that the invoice has now been sent. Note the due date of the first invoice is March 5th. Again, I'll switch to SuperUser to advance the clock to March 6th, which is one day following the due date of the first invoice. I click the Internal Tools tab. Here's the testing system clock menu link in the sidebar. I click in the date field. And type March 6th. Now I click Change Date. I need to go back to Server Tools to run a batch process. Here's the invoice due batch process. When I click Run, the batch process will search for all billed invoices with a due date of yesterday. Let's go back to Jeff Park. To refresh the display, I click the second invoice. Notice the status of the first invoice has changed from Build to Due. By the way, the invoice due batch process considers only invoices with a status of Build, so an invoice must be billed before it becomes due. This concludes our demonstration on sending invoices.
